Largely in line with expectation: For the quarter, while overall adj. net income was better than our expectations, total revenue missed expectations given lower Underwriting net earned premiums and revenues. Adj. EBITDA margin came in better than expected, primarily driven by lower amortization of deferred acquisition costs (DAC) in Underwriting, while loss ratio missed. Total members growth was in line, with independent members growth ahead of our expectations. Going forward, we would focus on Hadron's growth contribution to the exchange and how other partners can grow on the platform.

- Members: Total members grew to 248, up 33% YoY, in line with MSe. Independent members rose to 201, exceeding MSe of 195; Mission and Owned members reached 47, below MSe of 53. Underwriting Margin: Adj. EBITDA of \$16 million in line with MSe, and adj. EBITDA margin of 14.7% came in above MSe of 10.4%, driven by better than expected amortization of DAC. MGA operations: Revenue of \$58 million beat MSe of \$52 million; adj. EBITDA of \$24 million and margin of 41.8% also beat MSe of \$21 million and 40%, driven by higher direct commission income.

- Underwriting: Underwriting loss ratio of 72.7%, came in worse than MSe of 55.6%. Revenue of \$110 million was also below MSe of \$158 million, as net earned premium of \$71 million was much lower than MSe of \$134 million. Total Revenue: Revenue reported at \$219 million, below MSe of \$256 million due to lower Underwriting revenue. Exchange Services: Revenue of \$86 million was in line with MSe, while adj. EBITDA of \$56 million was slightly below MSe of \$58 million. Adj. EBITDA margin of 65% was below MSe of 67%.
